00:58:11.760 --> 00:58:21.600
Salman Rushdie did, or in architecture. It's
blasphemy. I don't think Yamasaki knew that,

00:58:21.600 --> 00:58:31.480
but what he was trying to do, because he was
Yamasaki, is he was trying to again, in my

00:58:31.480 --> 00:58:38.120
opinion; he was trying to justify his own
originality as an architect and as a human

00:58:38.120 --> 00:58:44.920
being in the face of an embarrassing compromise
